# Talegate Mobile — Cursor Rules

## Overview
This is a React Native / Expo (TypeScript) app. All design decisions flow from
the Talegate Design System. Before writing any UI code, read these rules.

---

## 1. Always use design tokens — never hardcode values

All tokens live in `mobile/src/theme/theme.ts`. Import from there:

```ts
import {
  colors, fonts, fontSize, space, radius, shadow,
  text as type, gradients, motion,
} from '../theme/theme';
// (adjust relative path as needed)
```

**Never** hardcode: hex colors, font sizes, spacing numbers, border radii, or
shadow values. Every one of those has a named token.

---

## 2. Colors

Use semantic aliases from `colors` — not raw `palette` values:

| Use case | Token |
|---|---|
| App background | `colors.bgApp` |
| Card surface | `colors.surfaceCard` |
| Sunken well / input bg | `colors.surfaceSunk` |
| Primary text | `colors.textStrong` |
| Body text | `colors.textBody` |
| Muted / placeholder | `colors.textMuted` / `colors.textPlaceholder` |
| Brand (primary actions) | `colors.brand` (indigo #423AA0) |
| Accent (warmth, highlights) | `colors.accent` (candle amber #E89B3C) |
| Danger | `colors.danger` |
| Hairline border | `colors.borderHairline` |
| Night bg | `colors.nightBg` |
| Night card | `colors.nightCard` |
| Night text | `colors.nightText` |

Rules:
- **Accent (`candle amber`) is for focal warmth only** — highlights, the "lit"
  chapter state, `.club` wordmark. Never use it for large fills or buttons.
- **Brand (indigo) is for primary actions, links, active states.**
- Night mode surfaces: `nightBg → nightRaised → nightCard`; text: `nightText`.

---

## 3. Typography

Use the ready-made `text` presets (spread directly into `style`):

```ts
// ✅ correct
<Text style={type.h1}>Tonight's chapter</Text>
<Text style={[type.body, { color: colors.textSecondary }]}>…</Text>

// ❌ wrong — never hardcode
<Text style={{ fontSize: 32, fontWeight: 'bold' }}>…</Text>
```

**Available presets:** `displayXl`, `displayLg`, `h1`–`h4`, `bodyLg`, `body`,
`bodySm`, `bodyXs`, `serifDisplay`, `readXl`, `readLg`, `read`, `label`, `labelSm`.

Font families — **always set `fontFamily`, never `fontWeight`** in React Native:

| Family | Use | Weight keys |
|---|---|---|
| Schibsted Grotesk | UI, headings, buttons | `fonts.sans.regular/medium/semibold/bold/extrabold` |
| Newsreader (serif) | Story text, reading | `fonts.serif.regular/medium/semibold/italic` |
| Geist Mono | Metadata labels only | `fonts.mono.regular/medium/semibold` |

Mono labels → **UPPERCASE, wide tracking** — `CHAPTER 04 · NIGHT 12`.
Everywhere else → **sentence case** — no Title Case Buttons.

---

## 4. Spacing

4 px grid via `space[n]`:

| Token | Value | Common use |
|---|---|---|
| `space[2]` | 4 px | tight gap |
| `space[3]` | 8 px | icon gap, small padding |
| `space[4]` | 12 px | chip padding |
| `space[5]` | 16 px | input padding |
| `space[6]` | 20 px | screen/card padding |
| `space[7]` | 24 px | section gap |
| `space[8]` | 32 px | large section gap |
| `space[10]` | 48 px | screen bottom padding |

---

## 5. Border radius

**Nothing sharp.** `radius.xs` (8) is the minimum:

| Context | Token | Value |
|---|---|---|
| Inputs, chips | `radius.md` | 18 |
| Cards | `radius.lg` | 26 |
| Large cards / sheets | `radius.xl` / `radius.x2l` | 34 / 44 |
| Buttons, pills | `radius.pill` | 999 |

---

## 6. Shadows

Spread shadow objects into style — **soft, warm-tinted, low-opacity**:

```ts
style={[styles.card, shadow.md]}
```

`shadow.none / xs / sm / md / lg / xl` — use `md` for most cards.
`shadow.glow` — candle amber glow, for focal/active brand elements at night only.

---

## 7. Gradients

Use with `expo-linear-gradient`:

```ts
import { LinearGradient } from 'expo-linear-gradient';
import { gradients } from '../theme/theme';

<LinearGradient {...gradients.dusk} style={StyleSheet.absoluteFill} />
```

- `gradients.dusk` — sage→wheat→peach→lilac. **The hero motif.** Use large and
  quiet behind bold dark type (launch screens, story headers, Shelf backdrop).
- `gradients.night` — indigo→plum→amber. Reader chapter intro, splash.
- `gradients.glow` — radial amber. Behind focal cover art / active character.

**Never** use: harsh saturated gradients, blue-purple "AI" gradients, neon.

---

## 8. Existing UI components — use before building new ones

`mobile/src/components/ui.tsx` exports:

```
Screen          — SafeAreaView + parchment bg, scroll optional
Title           — h1 preset
Heading         — h2 preset
Body            — body, accepts dim prop
Caption         — bodySm + muted
Label           — mono UPPERCASE label
Reading         — serif Newsreader read preset
Card            — elevation sm|md|lg, onNight, interactive, onPress
Button          — variant primary|accent|secondary|ghost|danger, size sm|md|lg
Field           — labeled TextInput
TagInput        — comma-delimited tag entry
Pill            — status chip, tone default|success|accent|brand
Avatar          — guild-seat initials, seat 1–4
Loading         — centered ActivityIndicator
```

Only build a new primitive when none of these fit. Mirror the pattern in
`ui.tsx` when you do: named export, spread `style` prop, tokens only.

---

## 9. Brand voice — copy rules

- **Sentence case everywhere.** Buttons, headings, nav labels, toasts.
  The only exception: mono metadata labels → `UPPERCASE`.
- **Tone:** warm, intimate, unhurried. Like dimmed lights at bedtime.
  Not hustle-y, not gamified, not streak-shaming.
- **People:** "you", "your guild", "guildmates". The group is a "guild".
  A story run is a "tale" or "chapter". The nightly drop is "tonight's chapter".
- **Emoji:** essentially none in product chrome. Only 🌙 as a rare brand
  garnish (e.g. push notification suffix). Never inline in sentences.
- **Numbers:** meaningful only — "Night 12 of 30", "3 of 4 chose." No vanity metrics.

Good examples:
- Empty state: *"No tale yet. Pick one tonight — your guild reads at 10."*
- Locked choice: *"Your word is sealed. The others have until 10pm."*
- Notification: *"Tonight's chapter is lit. 🌙"*

---

## 10. What NOT to do

```ts
// ❌ hardcoded color
backgroundColor: '#423AA0'
// ✅
backgroundColor: colors.brand

// ❌ fontWeight in RN
fontWeight: 'bold'
// ✅
fontFamily: fonts.sans.bold

// ❌ sharp corners
borderRadius: 4
// ✅
borderRadius: radius.sm  // 12 minimum for cards

// ❌ magic spacing number
padding: 20
// ✅
padding: space[6]

// ❌ invented accent color
color: '#FF6B6B'
// ✅ use danger, success, or guild seat colors from theme

// ❌ Title Case Button
<Button title="Create Guild" />
// ✅
<Button title="Create guild" />
```

---

## 11. File / folder conventions

```
mobile/
  app/            Expo Router screens (file-based routing)
  src/
    components/   Shared UI — ui.tsx for primitives, one file per feature component
    lib/          API client, socket, helpers
    theme/        theme.ts — single source of truth for tokens
  assets/         App icon, splash, fonts (loaded by app.json)
```

New screens go in `app/`. New shared components go in `src/components/`.
Never put design values (colors, fonts, spacing) anywhere except `theme.ts`.
